<plot>Program looks at examples of reconstructive surgery, including: a Louisiana woman has a breast rebuilt following a mastectomy; a woman has her malformed jaw reshapen; and a 25-year-old auto repairman undergoes surgery to repair his splintered skull after being pinned under a fallen car. The program begins with a study of human development in the womb.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?544975</url></doc>
